President Muhammadu Buhari has finally signed the N30,000 minimum wages proposed by Labour into law. He said the payment of this new minimum wage will commence in May, 2019 to mark the international Workersâ€™ Day. Earlier in the week, the President had pledged to expedite the signing of the bill. The two chambers of the National Assembly had passed the bill and transmitted it to the President for his assent. The President had set up a tripartite committee to look into the demands of the organised labour. News Express